<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/5817950-angel-ine"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1310912175i/5817950._UX100_CR0,17,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/5817950-angel-ine">Angel &#39;ine</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">A pleasant Surprise! This book had a slower start than what i was used to but the story built up , took pace and blossomed into a beautiful finale. I <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">A pleasant Surprise! This book had a slower start than what i was used to but the story built up , took pace and blossomed into a beautiful finale. I have read many books with parallel/multiple story-lines but this one stood out in the sense that it was COMPLETE. Yup... no loose ends there to leave you wondering "what the heck happened or am i suppose to rely on my imagination?" Loved how the book leaves you with a sense absolute completion. All questions answered, all that you wondered about through the entire read will be revealed. Not exaggerated or over-hyped but a simple reality based story line. Very believable indeed. <br /><br />In all an enjoyable read that leaves you with a lingering sweet after taste.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
